cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a method for generating tableau inference rules for formal semantics of a logic, which is a topic closely related to logic in computer science.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the generation of automated decision procedures, which is a common topic in AI.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category as the paper discusses the generation of sound and complete calculi, which is a topic related to programming language semantics.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the automation of the generation of tableau rules, which is a topic related to software engineering.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses the generation of a terminating tableau calculus, which is a topic related to formal languages and automata theory.
